{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"11d0e14a-921a-412a-8a91-24e03c6be572","content":"The project doesn't exist yet, but I can tell you exactly what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish a .NET tool to NuGet.org:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for ...</Description>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nKey points:\n\n- **`PackAsTool`** — marks the project as a .NET global/local tool.\n- **`ToolCommandName`** — the CLI command users will run (e.g., `my-mcp-server`).\n- **`OutputType` must be `Exe`** — tools must be console apps.\n\n### Build, pack, and publish\n\n```bash\ndotnet pack -c Release\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_NUGET_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run it\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install --global MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server   # runs via stdio\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"92c46725-ebd6-4093-bcda-7c63258edc73","outputTokens":411,"requestId":"AC03:66EEF:E13A7C:117C8BB:6A012E1C"},"id":"04f94e5b-68b5-4ef0-b374-39dd163b298b","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:17:23.359Z","parentId":"652ed4a4-c13c-4f92-9306-c7d8352af55f"}
